    Be encouraging
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    My students seem to like my course. Sweet!
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    Your student enrollment rate was 76% higher than your industry average. Nice work!
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>Encourage and support users as they complete the process.</li>
    <li>Tracking is usually the most exciting part for users. Our personality should come through in this step.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="anchor-container">
    <a href="#blog" class="anchor"><span class="ion-link"></span></a>
    <a name="blog" class="anchor-text"></a>
    Blog
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    I learn something every time I read Intuo's blog.
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    We’ve added the blended learning to courses, so you can now take Intuo
    anywhere. The feature will be available, by the end of next week.
    We’re pretty excited about this.
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>These people know Intuo. Be casual with them, and have a sense of humor.</li>
    <li>Every post should teach readers something. Enlighten them with extra links, tips, information that makes them smarter, or sneak peeks into our office.</li>
    <li>Assume that readers are smart and tech-savvy Intuo users.</li>
  </ul>

