    Public site
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    Talent management is just what I need. I might sign up for an Intuo account.
    I wonder what features they have, and how much it’ll cost me per month.
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    Join more than 120 companies who use Intuo to track and increase the human capital of their company every day.
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>Be confident in explaining why Intuo is so great. </li>
    <li>Show people how easy it is to use Intuo.</li>
    <li>Delight people with design, data, and helpful information about Intuo.</li>
    <li>Relay our personality and sense of humor, but don’t go crazy (think clever, not silly).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="anchor-container">
    <a href="#legal-content" class="anchor"><span class="ion-link"></span></a>
    <a name="legal-content" class="anchor-text"></a>
    Legal content
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    I need to make sure Intuo isn’t going to steal my content before I publish my courses.
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    You retain ownership of the materials you upload to the Service.
    We may use or disclose your materials only as we describe in these
    Terms and our Privacy Policy.
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>Write as calmly and clearly as possible, within the obvious constraints. Only use legal jargon when it’s absolutely necessary.</li>
    <li>Don’t dumb anything down or joke around. Legal content is serious business.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="anchor-container">
    <a href="#calming-the-user" class="anchor"><span class="ion-link"></span></a>
    <a name="calming-the-user" class="anchor-text"></a>
    Calming the user
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    I need to get this course published ASAP, because my boss is breathing down my back.
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    Send now—this is your moment of glory.
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>Use language that empowers people to create courses.</li>
    <li>Encourage and support users as they go through a potentially stressful process.</li>
    <li>Provide a little comic relief, but don’t annoy or distract busy users with over-the-top humor or too many extra words.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="anchor-container">
    <a href="#failure-message" class="anchor"><span class="ion-link"></span></a>
    <a name="failure-message" class="anchor-text"></a>
    Failure message
  </h3>

  <hr>

  <h4>What the user thinks</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    What went wrong? I really need to get this course published.
  </p>

  <h4>How we should react</h4>

  <p class="quote">
    We’re experiencing a brief problem. Our engineers are on the case,
    and will have things back to normal shortly.
  </p>

  <h4><span class="icon ion-lightbulb"></span> Tips</h4>

  <ul>
    <li>Offer a solution or next step.</li>
    <li>Be straightforward. Explain what’s going on right away.</li>
    <li>Be calm. Don’t use exclamation points or alarming words like "alert" or "immediately."</li>
    <li>Be serious. Don’t joke around with people who are frustrated.</li>
  </ul>
